The paper discusses graph pattern matching algorithms for dynamic graphs, which are commonly used in social network analytics and financial network analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DB (databases) sub-category, which often deals with data management and analysis. Additionally, the paper proposes an adaptive optimization system based on reinforcement learning, which falls under the cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the computation complexity of graph pattern matching algorithms, which could place it in the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm using million-scale attributed and time-evolving social graphs, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.SI (social and information networks) or cs.LG (machine learning) sub-categories.
